# GLOW_HOST.bron — this host's toolchain and OS declaration.
#
# Copy this file to GLOW_HOST.bron at the repository root and fill in YOUR
# values. GLOW_HOST.bron is gitignored (personal, machine-specific absolute
# paths); only this .template is committed, so this works for anyone who
# clones the fork. This is Glow OS's own root config — the sibling, in Bron,
# to .claude/rules and .cursor/rules, but for the host and toolchain rather
# than agent behavior.
#
# Read by: tools/glow_host_run.sh
# See: external-research/20260714-005658_native-arm64-parity-witness-run.md
# (the RYE_ZIG/RYE_LIB PATH-fallback footgun this file exists to close)
#
# Worked hosts in this tree so far: macOS aarch64 · Linux x86_64 (Framework).
# Fill os/arch for the machine you are on; never copy another host's absolute
# paths.

# os: macos | linux | (uname -s, lowercased, first word)
os linux
# arch: aarch64 | x86_64 (uname -m; "arm64" reads as aarch64)
arch x86_64

# Absolute path to the pinned Zig 0.16.0 binary for THIS host's os/arch.
# Fetch + checksum-verify per rye/README.md before pointing here — never trust
# an unverified toolchain. After fetch, many clones point at
# <repo>/vendor/zig-toolchain/zig on this machine.
rye_zig /absolute/path/to/vendor/zig-toolchain/zig

# Absolute path to rye/lib (Rye's own standard library directory).
rye_lib /absolute/path/to/rye/lib

# The Zig version this toolchain reports (rye version prints it back to you;
# confirm they match before trusting a build).
zig_version 0.16.0

# When this file was last confirmed correct on this host (your one-clock stamp;
# timezone lives in GLOW_PROFILE.bron, not here).
checked YYYYMMDD.HHMMSS
